    {
      "name": "Todo",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Get all todos (with pagination)",
          "id": "e0faed80-1512-4ac5-a192-05bbe4b64c08",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Accept",
                "value": "application/json",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/{{todos}}?page=1&per_page=2&status=completed",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "{{todos}}"
              ],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "page",
                  "value": "1"
                },
                {
                  "key": "per_page",
                  "value": "2"
                },
                {
                  "key": "status",
                  "value": "completed"
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "### Description\n\nRetrieve a paginated list of todo items that match an optional completion status filter.\n\nThis request calls the todos listing endpoint using environment variables for the base URL and resource path:\n\n- `{{base_url}}` – The API base URL\n    \n- `{{todos}}` – The todos resource path segment (e.g., `todos`), combined with `{{base_url}}` to form the full endpoint.\n    \n\nFinal URL shape:  \n`{{base_url}}/{{todos}}?page=1&per_page=2&status=completed`\n\n### Pagination\n\nPagination is controlled via query parameters:\n\n- `page` (number, required) – 1-based index of the results page to fetch. Example: `1`.\n    \n- `per_page` (number, required) – Number of todos returned per page. Example: `2`.\n    \n\nThe server is expected to return only the items for the requested page, based on `per_page`. Typical responses also include pagination metadata (e.g., total count, current page, total pages, etc.)\n\n### Status Filter\n\nFilter todos by completion status using the `status` query parameter:\n\n- `status` (string, optional but used in this request) – Filter value (currently supports only `completed`)\n    \n\n### Expected Response\n\n- **Status code**: `200 OK` on success.\n    \n- **Body format**: JSON array or object containing a list of todo items.\n    \n- **Content type**: `application/json` (requested via the `Accept` header).\n    \n\n### Example Usage\n\n1. Ensure your active environment defines:\n    \n    - `base_url` (e.g., `https://api.example.com`)\n        \n    - `todos` (e.g., `todos`)\n        \n2. Open this request and verify the query parameters:\n    \n    - `page=1`\n        \n    - `per_page=2`\n        \n    - `status=completed`\n        \n3. Send the request to retrieve the first page of completed todos, two items per page."
          },
          "response": []
        },
